# =============================================================================
# COMMENTS FOR MAINTAINERS
# =============================================================================

# This .gitignore is designed to:
# 1. Include only essential distribution files
# 2. Exclude all user-specific configurations and runtime data
# 3. Exclude development artifacts and test results
# 4. Exclude system-specific files across all platforms
# 5. Keep the repository clean and focused on distribution

# When adding new files to the project:
# - Template files: Include with !pattern
# - User-generated files: Exclude with pattern
# - Development tools: Usually exclude
# - Core distribution: Always include with !pattern if needed

# Security Note:
# This .gitignore helps prevent accidental commit of:
# - API keys and credentials
# - User-specific configurations  
# - Test results with potentially sensitive data
# - System-specific files that could leak information